  "A similar thing to look out for is that you can't have variable names that have a \u0000SKIP#173\u0000 in them. So any normal HTML attributes that have a \u0000SKIP#174\u0000 in them (like \u0000SKIP#175\u0000) you need to convert to camelCase.": "",
  "Whenever you want to use an expression (something that produces a value) in JSX, you need to wrap the expression in single curly braces, \u0000SKIP#177\u0000.": "",
